  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Haiti SCLR and DRR Emergency Response for Earthquake Affected Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will fund 40 microgrant initiatives (23 of ACT funding, 17 of Code 3) using the SCLR approach in Camp-Perrin and Les Cayes where homes have been destroyed or damaged and livelihoods lost, and 2 DDR initiatives. The activities will include:
1. co &#x2013; design project meeting with Koral 
2. Identification of local response initiatives in affected areas through PALC facilitators 
3. Community groups apply for small response grants through simple application process
4. PALC facilitators work with community groups to adapt local inclusion, accountability and participation mechanisms  
5. Grants dispersed and implemented by local groups/orgs
6. Linking groups to training and capacity building</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This approach will focus on the natural resilience and abilities of affected communities and look to fund organic community-led micro projects using a cash modality which will meet their response needs. Up to 1,048 people directly will be reached in the affected communities of Camp-Perrin and Les Cayes.</narrative>
  </description>
